	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm sorry but that's really a poor way to view a potentially complex class.&nbsp;&nbsp;Clerics, when well played, can also root part, stun, atone, in lower levels lull, occasionally DA pull, and generally add a LOT to the combat capabilites of thier group.  As a chanter, my very best partner in the game is a cleric comfy with all of these spells.   Got a mob fixated on me and cant cast through to save my life? His atone will.  Got a mob I need to mez but I'm getting interrupted (and even at 56 that happens now and again) too much? His stun gives me time to mez.  Got a mob that CAN NOT be mezzed? I tash it off to a corner and take the pounding as he roots it there.  A good cleric can add 50% to my own effectiveness.. even as my work saves him 70% of his healing mana through mezzes and stuns and slows.<br><br>As buffs go long term it's more effective to buff folks... the only exception I would see is to use a somewhat lower version of the armour of faith line on non tanks.  Btw, enchanters are tanks, not melee no but yes tanks, in the true definition of the word, one who takes frequent poundings, and often chase AC to the detriment of minor things like int or cha.  Costs for symbol or runes should be borne by the whole party, rather than shoved off onto one person to bear the freight.  If the party is not willing to pay for them then there clearly was no need for them to be cast, right?<br><br>As mana goes, if you're haveing a hard time handling a mad puller, Lie.  Yes, LIE.  I often adjust my mana report up or down a bubble based on circumstances.  Up if I've just finished buffing and expect to recover pretty quickly, or have Theft of thought ready with casters expected, or know the pull/pacing in question (my job) and want to keep mobs split up by shoving the tank out the door now.  Down if I've a couple buffs expected in the next 2-3 minutes, or if I'm having a hard time with the current pacing and see the cleric having a harder one.  I strongly oppose having the mana bars presented to the group as a whole.. our edited version of mana available is far more likely to be accurate than a number on a screen sans the reasons behind the editing.<br><br>Meredeth, 56 enchanter<br>Chrystant, 14 cleric<br>Tunare<br>&nbsp;<br>Meredeth, 60 ench, Tunare</td></tr>
