	   <a name=96655486623715></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96655486623715><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96655486623715>RE: Clerics</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=96655486623715#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 7:27 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>I do not think the emphasis is on healing, but maintaining the health of the party, not necessarily the same.&nbsp;&nbsp;The primary application of mana is of course healing, but a stun can prevent damage, and costs about 1/3 of what a heal costs in mana.  Finishing off a creature with a nuke can even make a big difference, since your group may end up taking a superior heal worth of damage in the time it would ordinarily take to finish the monster.  <br> The spells of the cleric are all very well suited towards keeping the party alive.  Nuking just to damage the mob, no... but, knowing when to stun, when to med, the correct time to use that heal (yes, there is a wrong time to heal, as you will find out quickly), and when to finish off that monster with the only nuke you have, that is much more than just being the healer.  <br> The focus should be on keeping the party alive, not healing.  The two are the same sometimes, but sometimes not.  You just have to know what it takes.  <br> And ALWAYS, keep a reserve of mana.  Consider yourself OOM when you are down to a heal or two. Use that reserve only for emergencies<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
