	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just choked on your, "Don't be stingy with the symbol buffs, just accept it as an expense and use it on the tanks."&nbsp;&nbsp;What a miserable, cheapskate thing to say.  What about advising the other classes about abusing the clerics' wallets and contributing to the expense of keeping themselves alive?<br><br>Or why didn't you rather say, "Don't be shy about asking the members of your party to let you loot extra to cover the expense of their HP buffs" ?   It's advice I wouldn't heed ingame, frankly: I've only a couple of times had the courage to mention how broke I always am. At the mid levels, when the reagent was jasper and "only" cost 1pp per cast, it was enough to keep me broke.  Now I spend hundreds of plat on raids.  The three times I've actually kept count, the raid cost me 880pp (Fear raid), 600pp (Hate raid) and 1200pp (Sky raid).  In Sebilis I'm spending 110 - 150pp per hour to keep my party buffed (if they let me; sometimes the pullers get overzealous and keep me too low on mana), but at least by this level the other players have probably been exposed to the horrendous expense of the buffs (one round of peridots -- 60 to 78 pp) and it's standard practice to let the cleric masterloot and keep all the stones.<br><br>I know people who have 30 or 40 thousand in the bank.  I have never had more than 5 (right now it's less than 3), and I think that's mostly because of spending so much money on your protection.  I would like to hear how much other clerics spend on dots.  I know one who through guildsay admitted that he spent two or three thousand a week on them.  Do you spend two thousand a week on other players?<br><br>Just my two dots' worth.  I hope you'll understand why I'm posting anonymously: I don't want to become a pariah.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
