	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 20th 5:06 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sorry, but you should never do a buff round unless you're where you can med back to full before the next pull.&nbsp;&nbsp;You cast first on yourself, then med back up and maybe heal or stun during a fight.  When you're back to full, you cast on the next guy on your list.  For me, that's the guy who's the F2 key unless the tank is on the bottom, then I'll work from the bottom up.  Takes about six minutes to do a full round this way unless your party is out of its mind.  Twenty minutes later, when your own buff starts to drop, it's time to start a round.  You will generally come back to each character at about the right time, without their even asking for the buff to be refreshed.  This all falls apart if you're fighting where there's something that debuffs, and they'll have to ask you for a refresh.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
